# Job Cannon — Environment Variables (optional overrides)
#
# Since v5.1 (2026-05-21) the primary store for secrets is your OS keyring
# — Windows Credential Manager, macOS Keychain, or Linux Secret Service.
# The onboarding wizard and Settings UI both write to the keyring under
# service "job-cannon". Env vars set here OVERRIDE the keyring (useful for
# CI, headless installs, or scripted environments).
#
# Precedence (highest to lowest):
#   env var > OS keyring > config.yaml plaintext fallback
#
# Copy this file to .env and uncomment any keys you want to override.
# The app uses python-dotenv to load .env automatically.

# --- Flask session secret (optional) ---
# If not set, a dev-only default is used (fine for local single-user).
# Generate one with: python -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_hex(32))"
# FLASK_SECRET_KEY=your-secret-key-here

# --- AI provider keys (all optional — preferred path is Settings → keyring) ---
# Default cascade runs $0 end-to-end via Ollama → Groq → Cerebras → Gemini.
# Anthropic is the paid fallback; the CLI dispatch (claude -p) is $0 via
# your Claude.ai subscription. See docs/SETUP.md Section 3.

# Anthropic — https://console.anthropic.com/settings/keys
# Two names are recognized; ANTHROPIC_API_KEY is the canonical name and
# JF_ANTHROPIC_API_KEY is a namespaced alias to avoid colliding with
# Claude Code CLI's own auth in dev environments.
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-your-key-here
# JF_ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-your-key-here

# Google Gemini — https://ai.google.dev (free tier)
# GEMINI_API_KEY=your-key-here

# Groq — https://console.groq.com (free tier)
# GROQ_API_KEY=gsk_your-key-here

# Cerebras — https://cloud.cerebras.ai (free tier)
# CEREBRAS_API_KEY=your-key-here

# OpenRouter — https://openrouter.ai (paid; used by the cascade-audit judge)
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-v1-your-key-here

# --- Eval-harness provider keys (only needed for benchmark runs) ---

# SambaNova Cloud — https://cloud.sambanova.ai
# SAMBANOVA_API_KEY=your-key-here

# Mistral — https://console.mistral.ai
# MISTRAL_API_KEY=your-key-here

# Cohere — https://dashboard.cohere.com
# CO_API_KEY=your-key-here

# --- SERP / discovery source keys (all optional) ---
# These also have plaintext slots in config.yaml; env var wins if both present.

# SerpAPI — https://serpapi.com/manage-api-key
# SERPAPI_API_KEY=your-key-here

# Thordata — https://www.thordata.com
# THORDATA_API_KEY=your-key-here

# DataForSEO — https://app.dataforseo.com/api-access
# Format: base64(login:password)
# DATAFORSEO_API_KEY=your-base64-encoded-credentials
